title: For Sale:  ART 3-9x44 sniper scope
postcontent:
NEW in the box ART 3-9x44 Here is a chance to buy a VERY RARE, fully functional sniper Rifle Scope. This scope was designed by Jim Leatherwood, the famous designer/creator of the ART I and ART II sniper scopes used in Southeast Asia to enable a sniper with only moderate training to accurately shoot out to 800 meters without running through all the calculations and compensations to manually adjust for the ballsitics of the load being fired. Jim Leatherwood created the ART / MPC after the ART II, taking the knowledge learned with the military applications of his Auto-Ranging-Sniper scopes, and applying them in the design and productions of an Auto-Ranging scope for non-warfare use.
This particular ART / MPC has a low serial number (008775) and is complete with the mounting/ranging "saddle" that fits on Weaver and similar one-piece bases. This scope was manufactured under contract by Weaver Scope Company.
The ART / MPC is calibrated to automatically compensate for load trajectories over ranges from 200 to 600 meters. Unlike the ART I and ART II, which were calibrated for a single caliber and load, the manual for the ART / MPC contains settings for over 100 calibers / loads, ranging from the .17 Remington to the .375 H&H Magnum. 

Condition is new old stock! It comes with an inspection receipt, original box and copy of ART MPC manual VAL AT $1,200.00

title: For Sale:  Sniper scope ART 3-9x44
postcontent:
NEW in the box ART 3-9x44 Here is a chance to buy a VERY RARE, fully functional sniper Rifle Scope. This scope was designed by Jim Leatherwood, the famous designer/creator of the ART I and ART II sniper scopes used in Southeast Asia to enable a sniper with only moderate training to accurately shoot out to 800 meters without running through all the calculations and compensations to manually adjust for the ballsitics of the load being fired. Jim Leatherwood created the ART / MPC after the ART II, taking the knowledge learned with the military applications of his Auto-Ranging-Sniper scopes, and applying them in the design and productions of an Auto-Ranging scope for non-warfare use.
This particular ART / MPC has a low serial number (008775) and is complete with the mounting/ranging "saddle" that fits on Weaver and similar one-piece bases. This scope was manufactured under contract by Weaver Scope Company.
The ART / MPC is calibrated to automatically compensate for load trajectories over ranges from 200 to 600 meters. Unlike the ART I and ART II, which were calibrated for a single caliber and load, the manual for the ART / MPC contains settings for over 100 calibers / loads, ranging from the .17 Remington to the .375 H&H Magnum. 

Condition is new old stock! It comes with an inspection receipt, original box and copy of ART MPC manual VAL AT $1,200.00

title: For Sale:  Concealed Weapons Permit Classes Pensacola $75
postcontent:
The class is the NRA Basic Pistol / FL Concealed Weapons Permit class.  It covers safety, hands on classroom training, live fire training at the range, personal gun selection, cleaning/caring for a firearm and the laws/rules/procedures for the FL Concealed Weapons Permit. I also have a section of the class dedicated to personal defense with a firearm.  It is not necessary to own a firearm to attend the class as I have demo models.  If you own a firearm I recommend you bring it to class so you can train with it.  We typically spend 3 to 3 1/2 hours in the classroom and about an hour on the range. Once you complete the class you will receive a certificate that satisfies the requirements for the FL CWP.  You then fill out an application, have your fingerprints and picture taken and submit the application.  The cost of the actual permit is $70 and the fingerprint / back round check is $42.  The permit is good for 7 years.  I hold the public classes in the conference rooms at Homewood Suites by Pensacola Airport (or your location for a private class of 3 or more students).  The class is $75 per student and may be paid in cash, money order or local check.  

Here is a list of my current class schedule and registration link for them. You can register now and pay on the day of class.

title: For Sale:  Colt Python 1965 model shooter grade Nickel refinished
postcontent:
Cash Offers only:  To save on the guessing I don't expect an unrealistic price for this thing, So my head is not in the $1800 to $2000 range.
It is only worth what someone wants to pay for it.

This pistol has just been refinished to as good as its going to get.
Unfortunately, it sat in a holster for 30 yrs.
There was surface rust and some pitting, and the original finish was shot so i opted for the nickel refinish
It  is not flawless, in certain light you can see subtle specks of pitting on the receiver, barrel and inside of the trigger well, and a few other minor imperfections.
I will meet up with serious buyers for a full inspection and you alone decide on the purchase.
It does not come with a grip, you add one for $30 on up and make it look how you want.
I am listing all that I see in the interest of full disclosure and honesty.
Now for the positives, lock up, timing and action are perfect and everything is solid.
The owner passed 30 yrs ago and has not been shot since then, it is everything you expect in the 60's model pythons actions.

I am aware that removing a original finish diminishes the collector value, but believe me the original finish was gone already and it had no collector value left.

If you want a collector grade nickel or for that matter a 1965 python (if you can find one) to collect then plop down the $2500 to $3500 your going to pay for that piece.

I will let the market decide on this.
I will only accept cash offers and will send detailed pix to serious individuals since I can only post 3 here.

If I don't sell within a week of posting I will decide on any trade. Do not send me a trade offer at this time.

Leave me a number with your offer so I know you are a serious buyer, I know that Armslist is full of scammer colt offers, but this one is legit, and I have had many successful transactions on here.
I also have other listings for corroboration.

If I'm interested in your offer I will contact you, if I don't respond I'm not interested.

title: For Sale:  sniper scope ART3-9x44
postcontent:
NEW in the box ART 3-9x44 Here is a chance to buy a VERY RARE, fully functional sniper Rifle Scope. This scope was designed by Jim Leatherwood, the famous designer/creator of the ART I and ART II sniper scopes used in Southeast Asia to enable a sniper with only moderate training to accurately shoot out to 800 meters without running through all the calculations and compensations to manually adjust for the ballsitics of the load being fired. Jim Leatherwood created the ART / MPC after the ART II, taking the knowledge learned with the military applications of his Auto-Ranging-Sniper scopes, and applying them in the design and productions of an Auto-Ranging scope for non-warfare use.
This particular ART / MPC has a low serial number (008775) and is complete with the mounting/ranging "saddle" that fits on Weaver and similar one-piece bases. This scope was manufactured under contract by Weaver Scope Company.
The ART / MPC is calibrated to automatically compensate for load trajectories over ranges from 200 to 600 meters. Unlike the ART I and ART II, which were calibrated for a single caliber and load, the manual for the ART / MPC contains settings for over 100 calibers / loads, ranging from the .17 Remington to the .375 H&H Magnum. 

Condition is new old stock! It comes with an inspection receipt, original box and copy of ART MPC manual VAL AT $1,200.00

title: For Sale/Trade:  Dillon RT 1200 Case Trimmer
postcontent:
Makes short work out of trimming large quantities of rifle brass.  Used once and trimmed 100 thirty-thirty brass, works like a champ.  However, I'm getting out of reloading.  Not included but available 30-06, 300 WM full length trim and sizer dies from Dillon $40 each.

The RT 1200B is used just like a standard size die. The big difference is that while you are pushing the case into the die to size it, a 1/4 horsepower electric motor driving a carbide cutter is trimming the case to length. Chips are drawn off through a vacuum manifold that clamps to the outside of the special size/trim die. (Vacuum cleaner and hose not included.) Outside diameter of manifold as 1.250"
The RT1200B is equipped with a quick-disconnect power cord; and it can be used on any standard reloader, single stage or progressive.
The RT 1200B trimmer motor for .222 Remington and longer cartridges, in 110 volt /60 hz.
